mozilla.components.browser.domains

Class DomainAutoCompleteProvider

  • mozilla.components.browser.domains.DomainAutoCompleteProvider

  • public class DomainAutoCompleteProvider

    Provides autocomplete functionality for domains, based on a provided list of assets (see class Domains) and/or a custom domain list managed by class CustomDomains.

    See Also:
    class Domains, class CustomDomains

    • Method Detail

      • autocomplete

        public DomainAutoCompleteProvider.Result autocomplete(java.lang.String rawText)

        Computes an autocomplete suggestion for the given text, and invokes the provided callback, passing the result.

        Parameters:
        rawText - text to be auto completed
        Returns:
        the result of auto-completion. If no match is found an empty result object is returned.

      • initialize

        public void initialize(android.content.Context context,
                       boolean useShippedDomains,
                       boolean useCustomDomains,
                       boolean loadDomainsFromDisk)

        Initializes this provider instance by making sure the shipped and/or custom domains are loaded.

        Parameters:
        context - the application context
        useShippedDomains - true (default) if the domains provided by this module should be used, otherwise false.
        useCustomDomains - true if the custom domains provided by class CustomDomains should be used, otherwise false (default).
        loadDomainsFromDisk - true (default) if domains should be loaded, otherwise false. This parameter is for testing purposes only.
